] id est, noli tu pro polluto habere. Do not thou pollute, that is, Do not thou call or count polluted, that which God hath made lawful. 'Tis the uſe of the Scripture, very frequently to ſpeak as in an effective or active ſenſe, and to intend only a declarative; and in the very ſame ſenſe is the binding and looſing to be underſtood, Mat. 16.19. & 18.18. for teaching what is bound, and what looſe; what lawful, and what unlawful, Lightf.

